# Mug Forms

Forms are JSON config files in `surfaces/<name>.json`. They deploy as live web pages. Submissions trigger a handler workflow.

Full API reference (all field types, condition operators, page branching, access modes, edit mode): `.mug/docs/forms.md`

## Creating a Form

**Form config** (`surfaces/<name>.json`):
```json
{
  "type": "form",
  "title": "Service Request",
  "description": "Submit a new service request",
  "submitText": "Submit Request",
  "workflow": "handle-service-request",
  "access": { "mode": "public" },
  "fields": [
    { "name": "name", "type": "text", "label": "Name", "required": true },
    { "name": "email", "type": "email", "label": "Email", "required": true },
    { "name": "message", "type": "textarea", "label": "Message", "rows": 4 }
  ]
}
```

**Handler workflow** (`workflows/handle-<name>.ts`) — processes form data via `ctx.params`:
```typescript
workflow("handle-<name>", async (ctx) => {
  const params = ctx.params as Record<string, string>;
  const email = params._verified_email ?? params.email;
  await ctx.notify.email({ to: "owner@example.com", subject: "New submission", message: `From: ${params.name}` });
  return { processed: true };
});
```

Workflows in `workflows/` are auto-discovered by `mug deploy` — no import needed.

## Form Config Fields

- `type` — must be `"form"`
- `title` — form heading (required)
- `description` — subtitle below heading
- `submitText` — submit button label (default: "Submit")
- `workflow` — handler workflow name (required)
- `access` — who can access (see Access Modes)
- `fields` — shorthand for single-page form
- `pages` — multi-page form (overrides `fields`)
- `editMode` — load and update existing records

## Submission Data (ctx.params)

- Field values by name: `params.name`, `params.email`
- `params._verified_email` — present with identify/auth access (email)
- `params._verified_phone` — present with identify/auth access (phone)
- `params._auth_row` — full row from auth table (auth access mode only)
- `params._edit` — `"true"` for edit-mode submissions
- File fields contain the R2 URL of the uploaded file — use `fetch()` in a workflow to download and process
- Locked field values are enforced server-side — submitted values are overwritten with the known source

## Field Types

**Text fields** — single-line input:
```json
{ "name": "company", "type": "text", "label": "Company Name", "required": true, "placeholder": "Acme Inc." }
{ "name": "email", "type": "email", "label": "Email Address", "required": true }
{ "name": "phone", "type": "phone", "label": "Phone", "placeholder": "+1 555 123 4567" }
```
Add `pattern` for regex validation: `{ "type": "text", "pattern": "^[A-Z]{2}\\d{4}$" }`

**Number field** — numeric input with constraints:
```json
{ "name": "quantity", "type": "number", "label": "Quantity", "min": 1, "max": 100, "step": 1 }
```

**Select field** — dropdown:
```json
{
  "name": "urgency", "type": "select", "label": "Priority", "required": true,
  "options": [
    { "label": "Low", "value": "low" },
    { "label": "Medium", "value": "medium" },
    { "label": "High", "value": "high" }
  ]
}
```

**Multiselect field** — checkboxes (submitted as array):
```json
{
  "name": "services", "type": "multiselect", "label": "Services Needed",
  "options": [
    { "label": "Cleaning", "value": "cleaning" },
    { "label": "Repair", "value": "repair" }
  ]
}
```

**Date field** — date picker:
```json
{ "name": "preferred_date", "type": "date", "label": "Preferred Date", "min": "2026-01-01", "max": "2026-12-31" }
```

**Textarea field** — multi-line text:
```json
{ "name": "notes", "type": "textarea", "label": "Notes", "rows": 4, "maxLength": 2000 }
```

**File field** — upload to R2:
```json
{ "name": "photo", "type": "file", "label": "Upload Photo", "accept": "image/*", "maxSizeMb": 5 }
```

**Calculated field** — auto-computed (read-only):
```json
{ "name": "total", "type": "calculated", "label": "Total", "expression": "hours * rate", "format": "currency" }
```
Formats: `"number"` (default), `"currency"` ($X.XX), `"percent"` (X.X%). Expression supports `+`, `-`, `*`, `/`, `%`.

**Hidden field** — invisible, always submitted:
```json
{ "name": "form_version", "type": "hidden", "default": "v2" }
{ "name": "employee_id", "type": "hidden", "prefill": { "source": "auth", "column": "id" } }
```

## Default Values

Any field: `"default": "pending"`. Lowest priority in fill chain (prefill > editRecord > URL param > default).

## Prefill

Auto-fill from auth row, URL params, or database:
```json
{ "name": "name", "prefill": { "source": "auth", "column": "name" }, "locked": true }
{ "name": "dept", "prefill": { "source": "url", "param": "department" } }
{ "name": "manager", "prefill": { "source": "db", "table": "departments", "column": "manager_name",
    "match": { "column": "id", "param": "dept_id" } }, "locked": true }
```
Auth prefill requires `auth` access mode. The runtime fetches the auth row (or runs the `query` if configured). Computed columns from `query` are available as prefill sources.

## Help Text

Display a hint below the field label. Supports `{{column}}` templates resolved from the auth row:
```json
{ "name": "hours", "type": "number", "label": "Hours Requested",
  "helpText": "You have {{available_pto_hours}} hours available" }
```

## Field Name Uniqueness

**Field names must be unique across the entire form** — including fields on different pages and conditional (`showWhen`) fields. Duplicate names cause silent data loss at submission. `mug form validate` and `mug dev` will error on duplicates.

## Validation Rules

Custom validation with user-facing error messages. Rules: `min`, `max`, `minLength`, `maxLength`, `pattern`. Values support `{{column}}` templates:
```json
{ "name": "hours", "type": "number", "label": "Hours Requested", "required": true,
  "helpText": "You have {{available_pto_hours}} hours available",
  "validate": [
    { "rule": "min", "value": 0.5, "message": "Must request at least 30 minutes" },
    { "rule": "max", "value": "{{available_pto_hours}}", "message": "Cannot exceed your {{available_pto_hours}} available hours" }
  ]
}
```
Template values that resolve to numbers are auto-coerced for `min`/`max`. Validation runs client-side per-page.

## Locked Fields

`"locked": true` — read-only UI + server-enforced. Submitted value is always the known source:
```json
{ "name": "name", "type": "text", "label": "Your Name",
  "prefill": { "source": "auth", "column": "name" }, "locked": true }
```

## Conditional Fields

Show/hide fields based on other field values:
```json
{
  "name": "emergency_details", "type": "textarea", "label": "Describe the emergency",
  "showWhen": [{ "field": "service_type", "op": "eq", "value": "emergency" }]
}
```

**Operators:** `eq`, `neq`, `in`, `gt`, `lt`, `filled`, `empty`

Multiple conditions = AND logic. Hidden fields skip validation.

## Multi-Page Forms

```json
{
  "type": "form",
  "title": "Client Onboarding",
  "workflow": "handle-onboarding",
  "pages": [
    {
      "id": "contact",
      "title": "Contact Info",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "name", "type": "text", "label": "Name", "required": true },
        { "name": "email", "type": "email", "label": "Email", "required": true }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "details",
      "title": "Details",
      "fields": []
    }
  ]
}
```

Auto-generates back/next buttons, progress bar. Validates per-page.

**Conditional pages:** `"showWhen": [{ "field": "type", "op": "eq", "value": "emergency" }]` on the page object.

**Page branching** — route to different pages based on answers:
```json
{
  "id": "triage",
  "fields": [],
  "nextPage": {
    "conditions": [
      { "when": [{ "field": "request_type", "op": "eq", "value": "emergency" }], "goto": "urgent" }
    ],
    "default": "standard"
  }
}
```

Simple routing: `"nextPage": "details"` (string).

## Access Modes

**Choosing the right mode:**
- **`public`** — open form (contact us, feedback, public intake)
- **`identify`** — anyone can access after verifying email (self-service requests)
- **`auth`** — only users in a database table (internal tools — employee forms, client portals)

**Rule of thumb:** if you have a table of who should access this form, use `auth`.

**Public** — anyone can submit:
```json
"access": { "mode": "public" }
```

**Identify** — anyone can access after verifying email/phone:
```json
"access": { "mode": "identify", "method": "email", "sessionDuration": "7d" }
```

**Auth** — only users in a specific table can access:
```json
"access": { "mode": "auth", "method": "email", "table": "employees", "matchColumn": "email", "sessionDuration": "7d" }
```

**Auth with computed columns** — use `query` to enrich the auth row with JOINs or calculations. The query replaces the default `SELECT *` lookup. Use `:identity` as the placeholder for the authenticated user's email/phone:
```json
"access": {
  "mode": "auth", "method": "email", "table": "employees", "matchColumn": "email",
  "query": "SELECT e.*, r.hours_per_year - COALESCE(u.used, 0) AS available_pto FROM employees e LEFT JOIN pto_rules r ON r.employee_id = e.id LEFT JOIN (SELECT employee_id, SUM(hours) AS used FROM pto_requests WHERE status != 'denied' GROUP BY employee_id) u ON u.employee_id = e.id WHERE e.email = :identity",
  "sessionDuration": "7d"
}
```
The computed columns are available in `{{templates}}`, prefill, validation rules, and `_auth_row` in workflows — always fresh, no denormalized state to maintain. `table` and `matchColumn` are still required (used for dev-mode user dropdown).

Session duration format: `30m`, `24h`, `7d`. In dev mode, `auth` shows a user dropdown; `identify` shows freeform input. Both bypass verification.

## Edit Mode

Load existing record, update on submit:
```json
"editMode": { "table": "service_requests", "recordParam": "id", "matchColumn": "id" }
```
URL: `https://<workspace>.mug.work/<form-id>?id=123`

## Prefill from URL Parameters

Any URL param matching a field name pre-fills it:
```
https://<workspace>.mug.work/<form-id>?name=John&email=john@example.com
```

## Breadcrumbs

When linking to this form from another surface (portal, etc.), add `?from=` and `?fromLabel=` to show a back link:
```
/request-form?from=/portal&fromLabel=Back to Portal
```
No `?from=` = no breadcrumb. `fromLabel` defaults to "Back".

## CLI Commands

```bash
mug form init <name>       # scaffold form config + handler workflow
mug form validate          # check form configs for errors
mug form list              # show forms and URLs
mug dev                    # start dev server — forms are live immediately
mug deploy                 # deploy to production
```

## Advanced: Dynamic Forms (ctx.collect)

For forms generated programmatically at runtime (fields depend on DB state, per-user forms), use `ctx.collect()` in a workflow. Dynamic forms require running the workflow before the URL works. In local dev, `ctx.collect()` does not persist — use static JSON configs instead.

For displaying submitted data back to users (dashboards, approval inboxes), see the `/portal` skill.
For custom branding (logo and accent color on forms), add a `branding` section to `mug.json` — see `.mug/docs/forms.md`. Individual forms can override workspace branding with `"branding": { "logoSquare": "files/logo.png", "accentColor": "#hex" }` in the form JSON.
